# NestJS Agentic Rules (@akr/api)

## Architecture
- Modular structure (Modules, Controllers, Services).
- Use Dependency Injection correctly.
- Use DTOs for request validation.

## Data Persistence
- Use TypeORM/Prisma for PostgreSQL.
- Implement Repository pattern if applicable.
- Define clear entities/schemas.

## Caching
- Use Redis for high-frequency data access.
- Implement CacheInterceptor where appropriate.

## Security
- Validate all incoming data using `class-validator`.
- Use Guards for authentication and authorization.
- Sanitize inputs to prevent SQL injection.

## Documentation
- Document APIs using Swagger (if integrated).
- Keep code self-documenting with clear naming and small functions.
